parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS actuator can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal vibrates or makes a "chirping" sound
the brakes grab or pulsate
the ABS and VSC warning lights illuminate
and the vehicle may experience sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inverter can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and become stranded, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
or the rear brake lights do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience other electrical issues, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience other issues, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system or other components can cause a fire, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often with no warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without the accelerator pedal being depressed
the vehicle surges or lunges forward
the brakes are unable to stop the vehicle
the vehicle accelerates in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle surges or lunges forward when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hybrid system malfunction can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle surges or lunges forward
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle's power meter jumps to full power.
